                                        <h1 class="book-page-heading">Problem A<br/>Illuminated Lights</h1>
                                                                                    
  <div class="problembody">
    <p>There are <span class="tex2jax_process">$n$</span> lights in
    a row, all initially turned off. Some lights, when turned on,
    will illuminate themselves and all lights to their left. The
    others, when turned on, will illuminate themselves and all
    lights to their right. What is the minimal number of lights you
    need to turn on to illuminate all <span class=
    "tex2jax_process">$n$</span> lights?</p>
    <center>
      <img src=
      "/problems/illuminatedlights/file/statement/en/img-0001.png"
      alt="\includegraphics[scale=0.5]{lights.png}" style=
      "width:; height:">
    </center>
    <p>This image shows the result of turning on the fourth light
    in the first sample case. The first four lights are
    illuminated, and everything else is not.</p>
    <h2>Input</h2>
    <p>The first line of the input contains a single integer
    <span class="tex2jax_process">$t$</span> (<span class=
    "tex2jax_process">$1 \le t \le 10^4$</span>)&nbsp;—the number
    of test cases. The description of the test cases follows.</p>
    <p>The first line of each test case contains a single integer
    <span class="tex2jax_process">$n$</span> (<span class=
    "tex2jax_process">$1 \le n \le 2\cdot 10^5$</span>)&nbsp;—the
    number of lights.</p>
    <p>The next line of each test case contains a string
    <span class="tex2jax_process">$s$</span> consisting of
    <span class="tex2jax_process">$n$</span> characters
    <span class="tex2jax_process">$L$</span> and <span class=
    "tex2jax_process">$R$</span>, indicating whether the lights are
    pointed to the left or right.</p>
    <p>It is guaranteed that the sum of <span class=
    "tex2jax_process">$n$</span> over all test cases does not
    exceed <span class="tex2jax_process">$2\cdot 10^5$</span>.</p>
    <h2>Output</h2>
    <p>For each test case, output a single integer&nbsp;—the
    minimal number of lights that need to be turned on to
    illuminate everything.</p>
